Class DefaultPropertyValueParser

java.lang.Object
in.testautomationstudio.commons.parser.DefaultPropertyValueParser
All Implemented Interfaces:
PropertyValueParser<Object>
public class DefaultPropertyValueParser extends Object implements PropertyValueParser<Object>
Default implementation of PropertyValueParser used when no specific parser is provided for a PropertyKey.

This parser performs a simple pass-through: it returns the raw string value as-is (an Object reference). This is useful for bindings where the target field is a String or when a caller wants to receive the unmodified property text and perform conversion later.

Behavior

  • If the input value is null, parse returns null.
  • Empty strings are returned unchanged (empty String). Binding implementations should consider PropertyKey.defaultValue() before invoking this parser if they want to substitute defaults for missing or empty properties.

Example


 // Field will receive the exact string read from the property file
 @PropertyKey(key = "greeting")
 private String greeting; // will be assigned the property text
